ems is equal to their concerns.”--Christian Wiman, Poetry  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aAmerican poetry. 0aPoetry. 7aPOETRY / General.2bisacsh  atourism, poetry, poetic, poetics, poems, poet, war, wartime, trauma, 20th, 21st, century, contemporary, modern, present day, loss, grief, mourning, mortal, daily life, human nature, transpersonal, power, intelligence, moral, aesthetic, geopolitics, tsunami, winter, lamb, flag, liberty, election, bush, government, politics, meteor, minos, myth, ariadne, minotaur.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226900339423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226900339/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles